-- Even Construtora Rises as Sales Beat Estimates: Sao Paulo Mover
-- B y   F a b i o l a   M o u r a
-- 2012-04-17T22:12:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-17/even-construtora-rises-as-sales-beat-estimates-sao-paulo-mover.html
Even Construtora e Incorporadora SA 
rose the most in over two months after the Brazilian builder
reported first-quarter sales and new projects that exceeded some
analysts’ estimates.  Even climbed 5.3 percent to 7.58 reais in Sao Paulo
trading, the most since Feb. 1. The benchmark Bovespa stock
index  rose  1.2 percent.  Even said it started 516 million reais ($279 million) in
new projects in the first quarter, and signed contracts to sell
525 million reais of real estate, according to a preliminary
earnings statement posted on its website yesterday.  “Figures came in strong with Even reporting the best
operational results in our sample so far,” Guilherme Rocha,
Daniel Gasparete and  Vanessa Quiroga , analysts at Credit Suisse
AG, wrote in a report to clients. “Not only did launches come
in above our expectations, but sales were also strong.”  Credit Suisse rates the stock the equivalent of buy.  To contact the reporter on this story:
